        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 29 at 11:32PM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 1131 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 27
miles north of Orange Cove, or 32 miles east of Clovis, moving
northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Balch Power House, Fence Meadow, Tamarack Summit, Upper Burnt Corral,
and Dinkey Creek, as well as the Garnet Fire burn scar.
</description>
        <instruction>Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
